research

   We are curious, enthusiastic, determined, scientific, and interested in
   making a difference through science.

   Our research focus is the cryosphere - all things ice - and its
   interaction with the ocean, climate, and living systems.

   We use data from space, the field, and computer simulations to
   understand ice and climate change - now and in the future.

   Research areas:
     * Arctic system science (AGU Tutorial Talk)
     * Ice sheet - ocean interaction
     * Ice loss & freshwater flux
     * Ice - ecosystem connections
     * Hydrology of glaciers & ice sheets
     * Glacier & ice sheet dynamics

